{
  "stem": "9898.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But there were several gymnasias.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was one gymnasium-- it was a school for the men and one for ladies.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My school was run by the order-- Catholic order of the Silesian priests.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now, there were only three Jews in the whole school, and I must say we been treated very well there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I was-- until the end, which is the eighth grade, I was at top of the class.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And in the eighth grade-- this was the last year of high school-- we were 12 of us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I was top in the class, and all 12 of us went to the universities.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I remember one peculiar moment after the-- what we called the matura.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "This is the last [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I went to say good-bye to the principal, who was a priest, and I kneed before him, and he blessed me.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he asked me what my goal is.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I said, I wanted medicine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] says, oh, if you go to Krakow, would be very simple.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "You just go to our Silesian order, but you have to convert to [?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Catholicism. ?] I say, thank you, I'll try my best to do without it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Now, the life in-- in Aleksandrow Kujawski, this was a small town.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "There were Jews, and there were Poles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I didn't feel that anti-Semitism so much as it was in the other cities of Poland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I can only remember-- can never forget it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I can't get rid of it from-- from my mind.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "It was in 1920, after the war with the Bolsheviks, the army of General Haller-- part of it-- came to Aleksandrow.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And the first thing what they did, they caught all the Jews with beards and cut them off in the streets.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
